replies.body:
I use a bruiser/DPS Morde build myself. His base damages are really quite high, and with Mpen can be effective even late game with little AP in the overall build. His ratios suck for a burst mage and DFG is gone, so there's no reason to throw tons of AP on him anymore.

Unfortunately, there's little reason to build HP on him either. While more HP is good on every champion (except {{champion:16}}) Morde has less reason to build it than other champions. His shield is supposed to be the main thing keeping him alive, and it scales with resistances. His shields will stay up a lot longer when you have 150/150 AR/MR as opposed to 70/70 and 1000 extra HP. This means that while items like {{item:3151}} {{item:3116}} do give Morde some additional tankiness, %HP damage, and a slow, it's not helping his shield much and probably shouldn't be rushed.
Part of the reason I like the rework above is that it gives his shield some HP scaling so you can build those items guilt-free.

However, having extra HP or AP isn't a bad thing. My core items are {{item:3020}} {{item:3001}} {{item:3068}}. Runes and masteries give me 20% CDR. The MR shred from Abyssal increases the burn of the Sunfire, adding another layer of DPS on top of Morde's W. These also give him a great amount of Mpen and resistances, both of which are very important.
After those, it's pretty much whatever you need:
Need to kill tanks or just deal more damage in general? {{item:3135}} {{item:3151}}
Need some form of cc to help peel? {{item:3116}} 
Need to stay alive vs heavy AD? {{item:3075}} (Abyssal also increases the damage here too)
Vs heavy AP? {{item:3065}}
Want to split push? {{item:3512}} {{item:3060}}
Want to be a pain? {{item:3026}}

{{item:3152}} is still an item I'm on the fence about. Since this build revolves around shredding MR anyway, it's not going to be healing as much as before the recent change. Also, given that most of Morde's abilities are AoE, that's a huge reduction in healing on top. {{item:3146}} would probably be better for healing in the long run, but that's assuming that you build a {{item:3145}} in the first place. I find that a good supply of {{item:2003}} will be more cost/space effective to get you to the point where Morde is a high enough level that the health costs on his abilities cease to be a thing.

{{item:3065}} {{item:3152}} {{item:3116}} {{item:3151}} {{item:3023}} {{item:3020}} 
or if the enemy doesn't get much mr, switch out twin shadows and sorc shoes for {{item:3158}} {{item:3157}}
tanky as all get out, 1v5 teams.
